STATE BOARD OF MEDICAL EXAMINERS OF NEW JERSEY, PLAINTIFF-APPELLEE, v. GEORGE H. COLEMAN, DEFENDANT-APPELLANT. Submitted October 16, 1925 Decided February 1, 1926.

Before Justices Parker, Minturn and Black.

Eor the plaintiff-appellee, Grover G. Richman. Eor the defendant-appellant, Nathan Hale Berger. Per Curiam.

This case is substantially identical with State Board v. Maza, No. 443, of the present term, and for the reasons stated in that case, the appeal will he dismissed.
